description: Canola Fry Oil is a versatile and high-performance cooking oil that is ideal for deep frying and other high-heat cooking applications. Made from 100% pure canola oil, this oil has a high smoke point that allows it to maintain its quality and stability even under high temperatures. This oil is also low in saturated fat and high in heart-healthy unsaturated fats, making it a healthier option compared to other types of oils. It has a mild taste and a neutral flavor profile that won't interfere with the taste of your food. Canola Fry Oil is perfect for cooking up crispy fried foods like french fries, chicken wings, and tempura, and is also great for saut�ing and baking.
name: Canola Frying Oil

description: White truffle oil is a type of gourmet oil that is made by infusing high-quality oil with white truffle essence. It has a distinct and intense flavor and aroma that is reminiscent of fresh truffles and is commonly used as a finishing oil to add a luxurious touch to a wide range of dishes. White truffle oil is a versatile ingredient that can be used in a variety of ways. It is often drizzled over pasta dishes, risottos, and pizzas, and can also be used to add a delicious flavor to mashed potatoes, scrambled eggs, and roasted vegetables. It can even be used to add a unique and delicious flavor to popcorn or french fries.
name: White Truffle Infused Oil

description: Lemon Agrumato Olive Oil is a harmonious fusion of the purest extra virgin olive oil and the essence of fresh lemons. Each drop is a celebration of the zesty, bright flavor that defines this exceptional olive oil.It is produced by using only olives and citrus strictly free from harmful substances and carefully selected for ripeness and variety. The two ingredients are crushed simultaneously in a state-of-the-art frantoio (olive mill). When the resulting paste has obtained the right density, the Agrumato is extracted. The process takes much longer than is usual for producing extra virgin olive oil and the low yield makes this product rare and precious.
name: Lemon Extra Virgin Oil

description: This Golden Sesame Oil is an undeniably versatile staple perfect for breathing life into your favorite Japanese recipes. This imported oil is produced according a long-established technique to honor the tried-and-true custom. The oil begins with only the finest sesame seeds, which are first lightly roasted before undergoing a pressure-extraction process. description: Barbera Frantoio Olive Oil is a premium extra virgin olive oil made from hand-selected Frantoio olives grown in the rolling hills of the Piedmont region of Italy. It can also be used in cooking to add flavor and depth to a variety of dishes, such as soups, stews, and marinades.

description: Pomace oil is a type of cooking oil that is derived from the leftover pulp, seeds, and skins of fruits, such as olives, grapes, and other fruits, after the juice has been extracted. This oil is obtained through a process known as solvent extraction, where the remaining pomace is mixed with a solvent to extract the remaining oil. Pomace oil has a light, neutral flavor and a high smoke point, which makes it a good choice for high-temperature cooking methods, such as frying and saut�ing.
name: Pomace Oil

description: Introducing Omed Smoked Olive Oil, a premium quality olive oil that has been infused with natural smoke flavors to create a unique and delicious taste. This exquisite olive oil is crafted using traditional methods, resulting in a bold and smoky flavor that will elevate any dish. Omed Smoked Olive Oil has a rich golden color and a distinctive smoky aroma that will tantalize your senses. It has a smooth and silky texture, with a subtle hint of sweetness that balances out the smokiness. Made from the finest olives and naturally smoked using real wood, Omed Smoked Olive Oil is the perfect choice for grilling, roasting, and sautéing meats, vegetables, and seafood. It can also be used as a finishing oil to add a smoky twist to salads, dips, and marinades.
name: OLIVE OIL SMOKED

description: Extra virgin olive oil Frantoia is produced from the olive trees planted in the western Central Hills of Sicily. Three varieties of olives: Nocellara, Cerasuola and Biancolilla are used for this oil. Handpicked from the trees, they are sent daily to the olive press, where they are carefully crushed by traditional granite grinders. A cold centrifuge system is used for extraction guaranteeing maximum hygiene. Tradition and advance technology are joined together in the production of this elegant full bodied gold green olive oil, with a rich aroma, delicate fruity flavour and a slight aftertaste of sweet almonds.
name: Italian Extra Virgin Olive Oil

description: Introducing Omed Arbequina Extra Virgin Olive Oil, a premium quality olive oil made from the finest Arbequina olives. This exquisite olive oil is cold-pressed to retain its unique flavor profile, resulting in a fruity and well-balanced taste that will elevate any dish. Omed Arbequina Extra Virgin Olive Oil has a beautiful golden color and a delicate aroma of fresh herbs and green apple. It has a smooth and buttery texture, with a light peppery finish that lingers on the palate. Made from hand-selected Arbequina olives, Omed Arbequina Extra Virgin Olive Oil is the perfect choice for drizzling over salads, vegetables, grilled meats, or to use as a finishing oil for pasta dishes.
name: Arbequina Olive Oil

description: Almond Oil Leblanc is a premium culinary oil that is highly valued for its delicate and nutty flavor. Made from high-quality almonds, this oil is carefully extracted and cold-pressed to preserve its natural goodness and flavor, making it a popular choice for cooking, baking, and other culinary applications. Our Almond Oil Leblanc is made from premium quality almonds that are carefully selected and processed to ensure their freshness and quality. The almonds are cold-pressed to extract the oil, which is then filtered and bottled to preserve its delicate flavor and aroma.

description: Like every year, at the beginning of the harvest, the millstones of the oil presses start their work without rest. The millstone made of colombina stone, rotating on the pilla, will produce the miracle of the oil birth. Terre Bormane presents the extra virgin olive oil Colombino obtained by the simple pressure of wholesome olives carefully selected. Colombino is a excellent virgin olive oil with a full and palatable taste and an intense gold colour. It is not filtered, just subjected to customary, periodic decantings; a veil on the bottom of the bottle is a sign of genuineness.

description: Ligurian olive oil with a clean, light fruity taste is pressed from fully-ripened olives, giving it a golden color and sweet flavor. A filtered oil, Raineri “Silver Foil” has a slight peppery taste, but is agreeably mild because the olives are harvested late in the season. This oil makes a beautifully-balanced vinaigrette. for salad or to use in a finishing sauce for seafood or meats. The foil covering helps block sunlight, and keep the oil fresh-tasting.
name: Silver Italian Extra Virgin Olive Oil

description: This expeller-pressed Soybean Oil is a veritable behind-the-scenes kitchen hero. With a smoke point above that of canola or vegetable oil, this neutral oil stands up to high temperatures so you can fry and sauté to your heart’s delight. This oil is also ideal for baking, sauces, and cold applications, making it a truly versatile staple. With zero grams of trans fat per serving and no cholesterol or salt, this pure oil is the real deal!
name: Non-GMO Expeller Soybean Oil

description: Monini Granfruttato Premium Extra Virgin Olive Oil, a premium quality olive oil made from the finest Italian olives. This exquisite olive oil is crafted using traditional methods, resulting in a rich and fruity flavor that is perfect for a variety of dishes. Monini Granfruttato Premium Extra Virgin Olive Oil has a beautiful golden color and a fresh aroma of green olives and herbs. It has a full-bodied flavor with notes of ripe tomatoes, artichokes, and almonds, and a slight peppery finish. Made from hand-selected olives, Monini Granfruttato Premium Extra Virgin Olive Oil is cold-pressed within 24 hours of harvest to preserve its flavor and nutritional value.
name: Granfruttato Premium Extra Virgin Olive Oil

description: This pure avocado oil has a high smoke point, which means it's ideal for use in a variety of cooking situations. Use it to sauté vegetables for stir-fry, or you can pan-roast beef for your main dish. Put a little in a pan and grill up some delicious fish with a side of asparagus for a healthy, satisfying meal. Cube your favorite root vegetables, toss them in some Olivari Avocado Oil, wrap them in aluminum foil and grill for a flavorful addition to your table. The oil has a neutral flavor that will go well with any dish.
name: Avocado Oil

description: Iliada Greek Extra Virgin Olive Oil is pressed using Koroneiki olives from groves located on the slopes of Mount Taygetus located in the South of the Peloponnese east of Kalamata.  It is a smooth, fresh and full-bodied gourmet Greek olive oil, harvested and cold-pressed without the use of chemicals or preservatives. This Kalamata Extra Virgin Olive Oil ideal for fresh salads, grilled fish, white meat, raw sauces, pasta and vegetables.

description: Ligurian olive oil with a clean, light fruity taste is pressed from fully-ripened olives, giving it a golden color and sweet flavor. A filtered oil, Raineri “Silver Foil” has a slight peppery taste, but is agreeably mild because the olives are harvested late in the season. This oil makes a beautifully-balanced vinaigrette. for salad or to use in a finishing sauce for seafood or meats. The foil covering helps block sunlight, and keep the oil fresh-tasting.
name: Silver Italian Extra Virgin Olive Oil

description: This 100% fully traceable USDA Organic extra virgin olive oil is cold extracted within hours from picking unripen green Koroneiki variety olives, grown in the Messinia region of Greece. Smooth, fresh, and full-bodied, this extra virgin olive oil features notes of exotic fruit, ripe tomato, peach, and flowers. It encompasses an all-around robust flavor profile and medium bitterness with a pungent peppery aftertaste, while delivering a multisensory experience, striking emerald green color, and polyphenol antioxidants.
name: Organic Greek Extra Virgin Olive Oil

description: Introducing Omed Arbequina Extra Virgin Olive Oil, a premium quality olive oil made from the finest Arbequina olives. This exquisite olive oil is cold-pressed to retain its unique flavor profile, resulting in a fruity and well-balanced taste that will elevate any dish. Omed Arbequina Extra Virgin Olive Oil has a beautiful golden color and a delicate aroma of fresh herbs and green apple. It has a smooth and buttery texture, with a light peppery finish that lingers on the palate. Made from hand-selected Arbequina olives, Omed Arbequina Extra Virgin Olive Oil is the perfect choice for drizzling over salads, vegetables, grilled meats, or to use as a finishing oil for pasta dishes.
name: Arbequina Extra Virgin Olive Oil

description: Capezzana Extra Virgin Olive Oil, the epitome of culinary excellence and a chef's best-kept secret. Sourced from the picturesque hills of Tuscany, Italy, and meticulously crafted by the Capezzana family for generations, this olive oil is the embodiment of centuries-old tradition and unmatched quality.  It is characterized by a rich, fruity flavor with distinct notes of fresh grass, artichoke, and a subtle peppery finish that harmoniously dances on the palate. Crafted from hand-picked olives, this extra virgin olive oil is cold-pressed with precision to preserve its natural goodness and exquisite taste. It embodies the highest standards of quality, consistently delivering exceptional results in your kitchen.
name: Italian Extra Virgin Olive Oil

description: Red wine vinegar is a type of vinegar that is made from red wine that has been allowed to ferment. Red wine vinegar is a type of vinegar that is made from red wine that has been allowed to ferment. The wine is first exposed to oxygen, which causes the alcohol in the wine to be converted into acetic acid, giving the vinegar its characteristic tangy flavor. Red wine vinegar has a deep, rich color and a bold, robust flavor that is both tangy and slightly sweet. It is commonly used as a condiment, salad dressing, marinade, or in cooking to add flavor and acidity to a wide variety of dishes. It pairs well with meats, vegetables, and salads, and can be used in sauces, stews, and soups to add complexity to the flavor profile.
name: Red Wine Vinegar

description: Balsamic vinegar is a type of vinegar that is made from grape must, which is freshly crushed grape juice that contains the skins, seeds, and stems of the grapes. It is then aged for a period of time in wooden barrels, which gives it its distinctive flavor and aroma. Balsamic vinegar has a dark color and a complex, sweet, and tangy flavor that is often described as rich, syrupy, and fruity. It is a versatile ingredient that can be used in a wide range of culinary applications, such as salad dressings, marinades, sauces, and even desserts.

description: Vinegar de Banyuls Aged 5 Years is a premium quality vinegar that has been carefully crafted and aged for five years using traditional methods in Banyuls-sur-Mer, a picturesque seaside village in the south of France. Made from the finest grapes grown in the local region, this vinegar has a rich, deep flavor that is perfect for adding depth and complexity to a wide range of dishes. The aging process of this vinegar imparts a unique complexity of flavors, with notes of oak, vanilla, and caramel, resulting in a smooth, well-rounded taste that is both tangy and sweet. Its amber color and thick, velvety texture are testament to its quality and reflect the care and attention that has gone into its production. Vinegar de Banyuls Aged 5 Years is an essential ingredient for any gourmet kitchen, and is perfect for use in dressings, marinades, sauces, and reductions. It pairs particularly well with seafood, poultry, and vegetables, adding a rich and complex flavor to any dish.
name: 5 Year De Banyuls Vinegar

description: Acetaia Leonardi Saba the sweet, syrupy reduction of Trebbiano and Lambrusco grape must is a unique and versatile ingredient. The familys Trebbiano and Lambrusco grapes are grown in the 7 hectares surrounding the family home and acetaia. After a gentle crushing, the juice and pulp is coarsely filtered and the mosto (mash), is cooked (cotto) in an open cauldron at 175-200�F for over 24 hours, reducing it to about a third of its original volume. The majority of the concentrated mosto cotto is placed in a batteria to be aged and acidified into various balsamici. Leonardi selects are certain portion of the mosto cotto to become Saba. They age it in large oak casks for four years, thickening the syrup and giving it a deep complexity, without converting it to vinegar. The result is a pure, sweet, syrup expression of the Trebbiano and Lambrusco grapes. Saba has a fruity character, raisin-like sweetness, and hint of acidity that complements both sweet and savory dishes.
name: Saba Dressing

description: TB Aulente White Balsamic is a premium quality Italian vinegar made from Trebbiano grapes. It is a smooth and slightly sweet vinegar that has a distinct and delicate flavor, with notes of honey, ripe fruit, and a slight tanginess. This white balsamic is made by slowly cooking the grape must, then aging it in oak barrels for several years. The result is a vinegar that is smooth, yet full-bodied, with a golden color and a slightly syrupy consistency. TB Aulente White Balsamic is a versatile ingredient that can be used in a variety of recipes. It is often used in salad dressings, marinades, and sauces, and is also popular as a drizzle over grilled vegetables, seafood, and meats. It pairs particularly well with fruits and cheeses, and can also be used to add a tangy and sweet flavor to desserts.
name: Italian White Balsamic Vinegar

description: La Posada Sherry Vinegar is made from the finest Spanish sherry, a fortified wine aged in oak barrels, renowned for its distinct character and depth of flavor. The result is a vinegar that boasts a harmonious balance of sweetness and acidity, with a smooth and velvety texture that enhances a wide variety of culinary creations. With its complex and nuanced taste profile, La Posada Sherry Vinegar adds depth and complexity to dressings, marinades, and sauces. Drizzle it over fresh greens for a vibrant salad, use it as a key ingredient in a savory vinaigrette, or incorporate it into meat and seafood marinades to impart a unique and irresistible tang.

description: Rice wine vinegar, also known as "Ginsho" vinegar, is a type of vinegar made from fermented rice. It has a mild, slightly sweet and tangy flavor and is commonly used in Asian cuisine, particularly in sushi rice and salad dressings. It is a popular alternative to other vinegars such as white vinegar or apple cider vinegar due to its more subtle taste. Rice wine vinegar is often used to add acidity to dishes or to balance out sweet or salty flavors. It can also be used as a condiment for dipping sauces or as a marinade for meat or vegetables.
name: Rice Flavored Grain Vinegar

description: Vinegar Powder is a versatile and convenient culinary ingredient that is made from distilled vinegar that has been dehydrated and powdered. This powder provides a concentrated form of vinegar flavor that can be used in a wide range of recipes without the need for liquid vinegar. The vinegar powder is made by a process that removes the water from the vinegar, leaving behind a dry, granulated powder. This powder has a tangy and slightly acidic flavor that is perfect for use in a wide range of recipes, including marinades, salad dressings, seasoning blends, and more.

description: Seasoned rice wine vinegar is a type of vinegar made from fermented rice. It is a staple in many Asian cuisines and is known for its mild, slightly sweet flavor and distinctive aroma. The vinegar is typically seasoned with salt and sugar, which helps to balance its acidity and enhances its flavor. Seasoned rice wine vinegar is a versatile ingredient that can be used in a wide range of dishes, such as marinades, dressings, sauces, and pickles. It is often used to add a tangy and slightly sweet flavor to salads, stir-fries, and sushi rice, and can also be used as a condiment for dumplings and other savory dishes
name: Seasoned Rice Wine Vinegar

description: Jellified outside, each Pearl hides inside a liquid treasure. A bittersweet taste enriched by an exceptional aromatic power and a pleasantly acidity. The elegance and charm of these rare Pearls are now perfectly enhanced by a surprising new exclusive packaging to grab the attention of foodies and not only. It’s delicious with starters such as caprese, bruschetta, and an endless list of salads. Lovely on raw fish: try them on sushi, maki rolls, smoked salmon, and seafood in general. It’s beautiful on vanilla ice cream and fruits (strawberries, raspberries, peaches). And if you are looking to sip something special, add the Pearls to your cocktails!

description: DOP MODENA - THE ORIGINS OF THIS PRECIOUS DRESSING DATE BACK TO MORE THAN 2000 YEARS AGO, IN FACT THE ROMAN APICIUS IN HIS "DE RE COQUINARIA" REFERS ITS USE IN 60 PLATES AT LEAST. THE BALSAMIC VINEGAR OF MODENA IS OBTAINED BY A SLOW FERMENTATION OF COOKED MUSTS COMING FROM GRAPES OF ITS PLACE OF ORIGIN WHICH ARE OPPORTUNELY MIXED WITH PERCENTAGES OF STRONG WINE VINEGAR. IT IS NATURALLY AGED AND REFINED IN LITTLE BUTTS OF VARIOUS KINDS OF WOOD SUCH AS OAK,  CHESTNUT, MULBERRY, ETC., RESPECTING  THE PRODUCTION AREA HABITS. IT IS FIT FOR VARIOUS DISHES, FROM APPETIZERS TO DESSERTS.
name: Metista Balsamic Vinegar

description: Introducing La Marne Champagne Vinegar, a premium quality vinegar made from the finest grapes of the Champagne region in France. This exquisite vinegar is carefully crafted using traditional methods, resulting in a smooth and delicate flavor that is perfect for a variety of dishes. La Marne Champagne Vinegar has a beautiful golden color and a subtle aroma of grapes and oak. It has a balanced acidity and a light sweetness, with a velvety texture that adds depth and complexity to dressings, marinades, and sauces. Made from hand-selected grapes and aged in oak barrels for a minimum of two years, La Marne Champagne Vinegar is a versatile ingredient that can be used in a variety of ways. It is perfect for adding a touch of acidity and brightness to salads, roasted vegetables, and grilled meats.
name: Champagne Vinegar

description: Quince Vinegar has a lovely, aromatic scent of ripe quince and the scent of well made, clean vinegar. It can be used just as you would any white vinegar, but having the “cotogna” scent which I find intoxicating. The Cherry vinegar is a deep red color, with the scent of mature Marasca cherries, a lightly sour cherry with great body. This can be used for any recipe calling for good red wine vinegar. The cherry scent merely complements the clean vinegar flavor.
name: Quince Vinegar

Delouis offers many different flavors as well as sizes to suit all needs.

description: Introducing Omed Cabernet Vinegar, a premium quality vinegar made from the finest Cabernet Sauvignon grapes. This exquisite vinegar is crafted using traditional methods, resulting in a rich and complex flavor profile that will enhance any dish. Omed Cabernet Vinegar has a deep red color and a bold aroma of blackcurrant, oak, and vanilla. It has a perfect balance of acidity and sweetness, with a smooth and velvety texture that lingers on the palate. Made from hand-selected Cabernet Sauvignon grapes and aged in oak barrels for a minimum of six months, Omed Cabernet Vinegar is a versatile ingredient that can be used in a variety of dishes. It adds depth and complexity to sauces, marinades, dressings, and dips, and is especially delicious when paired with grilled meats, roasted vegetables, and artisan cheeses.
